        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 22 at 11:27PM CDT until April 22 at 11:45PM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 1127 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 10 miles west of Crowell to 9 miles northwest of
Truscott to 14 miles southeast of Chalk to 9 miles northeast of
Guthrie, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail is possible for the storm just
west of Benjamin, and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Crowell, Benjamin, Margaret, Thalia, Truscott, Gilliland, Copper
Breaks State Park, and Rayland.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
